Header: This is a CyCIF image of a biopsy from a patient with triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC) liver metastasis. This biopsy was obtained after the first infusion of Cisplatin (Cis) chemotherapy, before Wee1 inhibitor therapy.

Waypoints.Description: We observed high expression of phosphorylated CDK1/2/3/5 and low expression of pHistone H3 in pan-cytokeratin+ tumor cells after the first dose of Cisplatin.
Waypoints.Name: Cell Cycle

Waypoints.Description: Before Wee1 inhibition, only a few CD4+ and CD8a+ tumor infiltrating lymphocytes (TILs) were present.
Waypoints.Name: T cells

Waypoints.Description: In this biopsy, we observed a moderate number of CD14+ myeloid cells, in addition to CD68+ and CD163+ macrophages, prior to Wee1 inhibitor therapy.
Waypoints.Name: Macrophages
